Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez (D-N.Y.) to clutch their pearls ‚Äî and beg "The Big Guy" to once again "ignore" the Constitution.

So, my question is, when this case is resolved by the Supreme Court, should the administration follow that decision, if that decision ends up banning this abortion drug?"

You see, if a Liberal Democrat is president, his will "supersedes" that of Congress and the judiciary, whereas if a Republican is president and the Congress Liberal Democrat-controlled and/or the Judiciary comprises more liberal judges, the dictates of Congress and the Judiciary must override the president's positions.

It's just common sense, right?

Wyden tweeted that the abortion pill is "medication," clearly illustrating that many radical Democrats see pregnancy as an......"illness".

That is sick. It is, in fact, an "illness" that no pill can cure.

A sickness of the soul has descended on America ‚Äî a pandemic that is truly scary...and could be fatal.

By Frank Fang
April 14, 2023

Former President Donald Trump picked up his seventh Senate endorsement on April 13, with Sen. Ted Budd (R-N.C.) backing Trump‚Äôs third bid for the White House in 2024.

‚ÄúJust a few years ago America was strong, but now under Joe Biden, we are a nation in decline,‚Äù Budd said in a statement. ‚ÄúOur economy is faltering, our wide-open southern border is tragically wrecking lives, and our country‚Äôs power and influence in the world is diminished.‚Äù

In contrast, Budd said, the Trump-led America was much different.

‚ÄúUnder President Trump, our economy saw record-setting growth, and families were starting to get ahead. Neighborhoods were safer,‚Äù Budd said. ‚ÄúAcross the globe, we were achieving peace. We were respected by allies and feared by enemies.

‚ÄúThat‚Äôs why I endorse Donald J. Trump for President,‚Äù Budd added. ‚ÄúHardworking, everyday families need a return of the America First agenda to restore prosperity and peace.‚Äù

The six other GOP senators who have endorsed Trump‚Äôs presidential bid are Sens. Cindy Hyde-Smith (R-Miss.), Lindsey Graham (R-S.C.), Tommy Tuberville (R-Ala.), Markwayne Mullin (R-Okla.), Eric Schmitt (R-Mo.), and J.D. Vance (R-Ohio).

Budd Endorsement

Budd, a former House lawmaker, defeated Democrat Cheri Beasley to win North Carolina‚Äôs 2022 Senate race. Budd was endorsed by Trump before his November election victory, paving the way for his GOP primary win over former North Carolina governor, Pat McCrory.

Like many Republicans, Budd has criticized Manhattan District Attorney Alvin Bragg for bringing criminal charges against Trump.

‚ÄúThe Manhattan DA‚Äôs partisan prosecution of President Trump is a disgrace,‚Äù Budd wrote on Twitter on March 30. ‚ÄúNYC has a real problem with violent crime. Instead of spending so much time targeting his political enemies, Alvin Bragg should focus on doing his job to keep the people of NYC safe.‚Äù

On April 4, the former president was charged with 34 accounts of falsifying business records related to hush-money payments made during the 2016 presidential campaign. Trump has pleaded not guilty to all charges and stated that Bragg has ‚Äúno case‚Äù against him.

Budd introduced his first bill as a senator in February, when he and other GOP senators introduced the Build the Wall Now Act (S.422) in an attempt to address the border crisis.

‚ÄúPresident Biden has created the worst border crisis in American history. Instead of taking steps to solve this crisis, the Biden administration has tried to run out the regulatory clock on border wall construction,‚Äù Budd said in a statement about the bill.

He added, ‚ÄúThe Build the Wall Now Act ends this administration‚Äôs excuses and forces them to restart wall construction immediately. It‚Äôs time for a comprehensive solution to end the Biden Border Crisis, and this bill does just that.‚Äù

The North Carolina native also co-sponsored the Protecting Military Installations and Ranges Act (S.369), which was originally introduced by Sen. Ted Cruz (R-Texas).

‚ÄúThe increasing strategy, employed by nations like China, of buying up land near military facilities around the country is a direct threat to our national security,‚Äù Budd said in a statement. ‚ÄúAs a Senator from a state that has eight military installations and is home to thousands of active duty service members and veterans, this is a threat that must be directly confronted and stopped.‚Äù

Trump 2024

Thirty-nine House lawmakers have also chosen to endorse Trump for 2024, according to Ballotpedia‚Äôs endorsement tracker. These House members include Reps. Max Miller (R-Ohio), Mary Miller (R-Ill.), Byron Donalds (R-Fla.), and Elise Stefanik (R-N.Y.).

Apart from Trump, three other major Republican candidates have announced their 2024 bids‚Äîformer South Carolina Gov. Nikki Haley, former Arkansas Gov. Asa Hutchinson, and biotechnology entrepreneur Vivek Ramaswamy.

The former president is currently the leading GOP candidate, according to several polls.

A survey by Morning Consult, which polled 3,608 potential GOP primary voters from April 7 to April 9, showed that Trump had the support of 56 percent of potential Republican primary voters, with Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis coming in second with 23 percent of support.

‚ÄúThat 33-percentage-point lead over the past several days marks Trump‚Äôs largest since Morning Consult‚Äôs tracking of the hypothetical matchup began in December,‚Äù the survey says.‚Ä¶
